\frac{A}{z-\alpha} + \frac{B}{z-\alpha^*} = \frac{A}{-\alpha}\frac{1}{1-\frac{z}{\alpha}} + \frac{B}{-\alpha^*}\frac{1}{1-\frac{z}{\alpha^*}} = \frac{A}{-\alpha}\sum_{n=0}^\infty \left( \frac{1}{\alpha^n} z^n \right) + \frac{B}{-\alpha^*}\sum_{n=0}^\infty \left( \frac{1}{\alpha^{*n}} z^n \right)
= \sum_{n=0}^\infty\left[ \frac{A}{-\alpha}\left( \frac{1}{\alpha^n} \right) +\frac{B}{-\alpha^*} \left( \frac{1}{\alpha^{*n}}\right)\right]z^n = \sum_{n=0}^\infty x_n z^n
x_n = \left[ \frac{A}{-\alpha}\left( \frac{1}{\alpha^n} \right) +\frac{B}{-\alpha^*} \left( \frac{1}{\alpha^{*n}}\right)\right]
